3.30	Herborn	Herborn	Herborn is a historic town on the Dill in the Lahn-Dill district of Hesse in Germany. Before World War I, it was granted its own title as Nassauisches Rothenburg. The symbol or mascot of this town is a bear. Scenic attractions include its half-timbered houses; Herborn is located on the German Timber-Frame Road.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Germany_location_map.svg/170px-Germany_location_map.svg.png
